It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. It's the last room in the house that was only simply decorated.
Remove the ugly electric wall炉 and the furnace. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom order a wardrobe.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the chimney, and their bodies were all dried out :(
Get ready for the plasterer next week.
Satisfied with the small niche beside it.
Put the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet🙈)
Haha, look what we found behind the radiator!
Remember the adorable small vent added to prevent the chimney from getting damp.
Sweep has installed both the chimney cover and chimney cap. Those ravens that like to nest in the chimney should be safer now 🪺
The plasterer is done. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlay has been laid, and a toilet paper roll was even used as an attachment for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready to be laid. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break.
Hmm, today's progress has been a bit slow because cutting around the door frame to seamlessly connect with the hallway (which is also having its floor laid) has been quite laborious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me all along.
Finally done, but it's a mess! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are absolutely terrible. Finally, I can sleep well tonight!
The hallway floor and baseboards are still not done. The renovation workers won't come back for a month, so we can only make do for now, with just bare gypsum boards in the room.
Tonight, I did a quick DIY, using a coping saw and chisel to cut away part of the bottom of the door frame so the floor can be perfectly laid underneath.
The cork underlay in the hallway has also been laid.
We also finished laying the hallway floor yesterday! I got up at 5 a.m. today to go to Heathrow Airport and picked up Package 1, then took a nap, and now I can finally start installing the baseboards in the hallway. I'll grout after the adhesive dries.
